wikipedia_page.main: John Baptist Crozier,  (8 April 1853 – 11 April 1920), was a Church of Ireland clergyman who served as Lord Bishop of Ossory, Ferns and Leighlin (1897–1907); Lord Bishop of Down, Connor and Dromore (1907–1911); and Lord Primate of All Ireland and Lord Archbishop of Armagh  (1911–1920).
